In general, \systemname{}-cluster-reps considerably outperforms all other baselines on 2 of the 3 metrics (plausibility and distinctiveness). Our resource only comes behind Acharya et al. on the commonality metric (1.15 and 1.22 respectively), which is expected because Acharya et al. only cover a few relations about common rituals (e.g., birthday, wedding)